############################################################
# from EDIF schematic_implementation_model
############################################################
# The schematic_implementation_model schema describes the structural connectivity 
# and the physical implementation of a schematic view. 
# That includes definitions of 
# * schematic_bus, 
# * schematic_net, 
# * schematic_offpageconnector, 
# * schematic_onpageconnector, 
# * schematic_master_port_representation, 
# * schematic_master_port_bundle_representation, 
# * schematic_global_port_representation, 
# * schematic_ripper, 
# * schematic_bus_junction, 
# * schematic_net_junction and 
# * schematic_interconnect_terminator. 
# These structures are implemented on a page by specifying the position and orientation 
# of occurrences of various schematic templates specified in the instantiatable_object_model. 
# Bus and net structures are implemented by giving the associated graphics 
# and the display control information to allow the display of names and other attributes, such as criticality and delay. 

# ENTITY page;

# ENTITY page_comment_graphics;

# ENTITY page_border;

# ENTITY page_title_block;

